      <data key="d2">Ethnicity specifies the ethnic origin of patients in Clark.csv.&lt;SEP&gt;Ethnicity is a data column referencing the ethnicity information for patients.&lt;SEP&gt;Ethnicity indicates the ethnic background of endometrial cancer patients, with 'Not-Hispanic or Latino' as an example.&lt;SEP&gt;Ethnicity is a column in the Gillette.csv table recording participant ethnicity, with sample values such as 'caucasian'.&lt;SEP&gt;Ethnicity is a column in the Krug table describing the subject's ethnic background, primarily black or white.&lt;SEP&gt;Ethnicity is a column capturing the ethnicity of the patient.&lt;SEP&gt;Ethnicity is a column in the Satpathy table detailing the patient's ethnic background, with values such as 'caucasian'.</data>
