    <node id="Dou.csv">
      <data key="d0">Dou.csv</data>
      <data key="d1">content</data>
      <data key="d2">Dou.csv is a data file that serves as a comprehensive repository for detailed clinical, genomic, and proteomic information specific to endometrial cancer patients. The dataset consists of the Dou table, which integrates a wide spectrum of data types, including patient identifiers, demographic information, clinical characteristics, and extensive molecular measurements. Among the clinical variables, the file includes essential patient-level clinical traits and histopathological details, supporting accurate classification and investigation of endometrial cancer subtypes.

In addition to the core clinical, genomic, and proteomic data, Dou.csv encompasses supplementary data such as cell type proportions and, where available, relevant clinical scores for patients. The structured, tabular format of Dou.csv makes it well-suited for multifaceted research and analytics, offering researchers a platform to conduct integrative and advanced studies into patient profiles, disease mechanisms, and molecular associations.

Dou.csv's thorough integration of demographic, clinical, and molecular information makes it a valuable resource for cancer research communities focused on endometrial cancer. Its comprehensive annotation and patient-level granularity facilitate robust analysis, such as stratification of disease subtypes and understanding correlations across clinical and molecular domains. Overall, Dou.csv is regarded as an important tool for supporting advanced clinical and molecular investigations in the field of endometrial cancer research.&lt;SEP&gt;Dou.csv is a table in source11 that contains detailed clinical, genomic, and proteomic data for endometrial cancer patients, including patient identifiers, demographic information, clinical characteristics, and omics datasets.</data>
