    <node id="Endometrial Cancer Patients">
      <data key="d0">Endometrial Cancer Patients</data>
      <data key="d1">person</data>
      <data key="d2">Endometrial Cancer Patients are individuals diagnosed with endometrial cancer whose clinical, genomic, proteomic, molecular, and demographic data have been systematically collected and documented. These patients serve as the central subjects in datasets compiled for research, most notably in a dataset referred to as the Dou table or Dou.csv. Both terms, Dou table and Dou.csv, denote the same comprehensive data repository, which is used for the study and analysis of endometrial cancer patients.

Within the Dou.csv table, extensive information is recorded, including clinical profiles detailing patients’ medical histories and conditions, genomic data capturing genetic variations, proteomic measurements reflecting protein expression, molecular characteristics, and demographic details. The dataset includes biological samples from these individuals, which have undergone meticulous analysis to generate robust, multidimensional data.

Dou.csv is designed as a pivotal resource to facilitate in-depth research into endometrial cancer, supporting the integration of varied data types for holistic investigation. This table incorporates relevant records as part of broader research efforts, including its inclusion in research contexts such as Source11. By consolidating clinical, genomic, proteomic, molecular, and demographic data, the Dou table/Dou.csv provides a valuable platform for advancing understanding of endometrial cancer patients and supports a wide range of scientific analyses.</data>
