    <node id="Dou">
      <data key="d0">Dou</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">Dou is a data table, specifically referred to as "Dou.csv," that aggregates comprehensive clinical, genomic, and proteomic data for endometrial cancer patients. This table serves as a rich resource, capturing a broad spectrum of information relevant to both demographic and biomedical research contexts.

The Dou table includes columns with patient identifiers and essential demographic details, such as age and other patient-related attributes. In addition, it encompasses a range of clinical characteristics, which can include diagnosis, treatment data, and clinical outcomes. Beyond these, Dou offers extensive molecular data, covering genomic and proteomic profiles that facilitate in-depth analyses of cancer biology.

A distinctive feature of the Dou table is its inclusion of columns focused on immune cell proportions and various cell-type metrics, allowing for detailed cellular microenvironment studies. The dataset also contains multiple biological and molecular scorings, alongside a variety of additional molecular and clinical features.

Referenced as a primary data source in various research contexts, such as "source11," Dou.csv stands out as a multifaceted and integrated data table supporting advanced analysis of endometrial cancer through the aggregation of clinical, genomic, proteomic, immunological, and molecular information.</data>
