    <edge source="Dou.csv" target="Endometrial Cancer Patients">
      <data key="d7">11.0</data>
      <data key="d8">The relation (Dou.csv, Endometrial Cancer Patients) refers to the dataset Dou.csv, which serves as a comprehensive resource containing information about endometrial cancer patients. Dou.csv provides detailed clinical, genomic, and proteomic data entries related to these patients, capturing a broad scope of their medical information.

Within Dou.csv, data are organized in the form of the Dou table and its associated columns. This structure includes patient identifiers and demographic details, ensuring each patient entry can be uniquely distinguished and contextualized. Clinical characteristics, such as disease progression, treatment histories, and outcomes, are also recorded, enabling robust patient profiling and analysis.

Beyond clinical data, Dou.csv encompasses genomic and proteomic information, allowing for the integration of molecular profiles with clinical observations. This multidimensional dataset aims to facilitate advanced research into endometrial cancer by providing a holistic view of patient data. Each entry in Dou.csv reflects the complex interplay of clinical and molecular characteristics vital for understanding the variability and progression of endometrial cancer in diverse patient populations.&lt;SEP&gt;Dou.csv contains detailed clinical, genomic, and proteomic data for endometrial cancer patients.&lt;SEP&gt;Dou.csv contains clinical, genomic, and proteomic data about endometrial cancer patients.&lt;SEP&gt;Dou.csv contains clinical, genomic, and proteomic information about endometrial cancer patients.</data>
